
[1]allophane

   AL'LOPHANE, n. [Gr. other and to appear.]

   A mineral of a blue, and sometimes of a green or brown color, which
   occurs massive, or in imitative shapes. It gelatinizes in acids.

   Allophane is a variety of clay, occurring in amorphous, botryoidal or
   reniform masses.
